subSubSection.paragraph:
F e m a l e t e r m i n a l i a (
fig. 22
). Both spermathecae identical, dark brown, its width 1.45× maximum height; basal collar strongly sclerotized, ring-shaped, widening to base of spermatheca; internal duct invagination reaching 0.65 height of spermatheca. Blade of hypogynium 1.15× as long as proctiger with cerci. Blade of hypogynium acute apically, denticles on outer margin small, sparce and blunt, scarcely visible, directed apically, inner margin and membrane without scales.
